issues.summary: Environment containers must be run under unprivileged user identities
issues.description: Presently containers in Subutai run as the root user. This is a big security hazard. The container should instead run as a non-root user with the identity of the environment, owned by some user. This prevents the potential of a user in a container gaining access as root in the resource host.
issues.creator: dilshat.aliev

issues.summary: Kurjun must enable secure apt repository access with custom package exposition based on client identity.
issues.description:
Kurjun is intended to be a light weight Apt repository management system that can be incorporated into any Java based application or service as a component. The primary aim of the Kurjun is to provide an optional high degree of security without compromising a high degree of flexibility while sharing packages. By default apt clients use normal HTTP to access repositories and their contents. With HTTP, apt clients are anonymous without requiring authentication. Anyone can access the repository, and this might not be wanted depending on the packages that are exposed.
In addition to anonymous HTTP access, Kurjun allows for client and server identification via HTTPS access by leveraging PGP keys for bi-directional authentication. This allows repository managers to allow or deny access to the repository's contents based on the Web of Trust model using PGP digital signatures. In addition, role based access control (RBAC) can be used to enable fine grained access controls to the individual packages in the repository. This may serve useful for many purposes: private sharing, access/installation tracking, non-repudiation, digital rights management, and fine grained control over what can be exposed to physical and virtual machines in a corporate environment.
To facilitate bi-directional authentication a modified version of apt is included in the Kurjun which will included in our management server and resource host operating system distributions which uses PGP keys to authenticate against Kurjun services using HTTPS.
issues.creator: dilshat.aliev

issues.summary: The Subutai UI must be redesigned to be lighter, more user-friendly, ergonomic and modern
issues.description:
The UI as it stands was created just to expose raw feature for testing purposes, NOT for the ease of use of a user. We are assembling a specific UI/UX team to address these issues of usability and to assist in this redesign. This will have a dramatic affect on users of the Subutai Product. Ease of use means greater adoption. The management console UI needs to be redesigned for usability and ergonomics so that just about anyone can use it. Secondly we've realized that the choice of UI components and frameworks are unnecessarily heavy. We would like to shrink this footprint down as much as possible so the management console gets lighter while being redesigned. This must be handled immediately before any press on the project and on the product are made or else the first impression will be very poor.

This is part of Subutai project
issues.creator: kjoldoshbekova
